///////////////
// ========= //
// AREA INFO //
// ========= //
///////////////

@300400 = ~The water here is so dirty that you're not sure if you'll emerge from a swim unscathed. Everything floats here, literally.~
@300401 = ~An object of unknown purpose. Although there is no water in it, something makes you think it is a... fountain.~
@300402 = ~Whatever it used to be... is long gone.~
@300403 = ~A large, stone statue of a beautiful, but elegant and wise-looking goddess. She rests her hand on a magnificent shield.~
@300404 = ~The sign before you marks the entrance to an inn called Rivergate.~
@300405 = ~The sign before you marks the entrance to an inn called The Styx Oarsman.~
@300406 = ~A mysterious statue.~
@300407 = ~This bloody, intricate altar is dedicated to Blibdoolpoolp, the Sea Mother. Scattered shards of gems and pearls lie among the dark stains, but the blood leaves no doubt about what truly transpired here. The priests of this cult do not shy away from human sacrifice.~
@300408 = ~This is a system of aquariums arranged in a vertical wooden structure. Inside, you can see fish, crabs, snails and other creatures. It's an unusual and impractical design.~
@300409 = ~Two beautiful flowers grow from a rock that juts out of the rancid water. You can't quite decide whether the sight is beautiful or macabre.~
@300410 = ~In eerie silence, water spills over the edge of Sigil. There is no easier route to the Cage's edge, but a jump from here would likely mean disappearing forever. The implication offers a grim explanation for the name of this place.~
@300411 = ~This machine illustrates the relationship between crystal balls in the Prime Material Plane. The knowledge is entirely useless in Sigil, unless one is attempting to summon something from the Prime.~
@300412 = ~A machine powered by gears hidden beneath the floor. You have no idea what it's used for.~
@300413 = ~In the center of this dilapidated and dirty temple stands a statue of a giant wererat.~
@300414 = ~This tall mast is devoid of sails, not that the Styx Oarsman has anything to sail on at the moment. From the crow's nest, an incredible panorama of the Ditch is visible.~
@300415 = ~The books on the shelves are arranged alphabetically by category. Depending on one's needs, one can find fiction, nonfiction, historical annals, legal documents, copies of political treatises, and even dark grimoires on demonology and witchcraft.~
@300416 = ~One of the many goddesses of love, probably from the Prime Material Plane. Someone has painted her symbol on a cliff with cheap paint, which will likely disappear in a few months.~
@300417 = ~Below, another earthberg floats, topped by a circular wooden port-city. High cliffs and waterfalls surround it, and on one side it meets the ocean, which seems impossibly suspended in space.~
@300418 = ~This impressive golden statue depicts a one-eyed god wielding a spear. Its craftsmanship is dazzling.~
@300419 = ~These banners display the crest of the Fated: a crowned, robed humanoid figure.~
@300420 = ~This bust, crafted with *incredible* attention to detail, depicts a woman wearing a winged helmet. It emanates an aura of power and loss.~
@300421 = ~This stone likely has some ritual significance. The runes visible here appear to be protective.~
@300422 = ~This is a sauna heater that warms the cabin. It is fired by wood, which heats the stones that store the heat. These stones then release it into the surrounding air and produce steam when water is poured over them.~
@300423 = ~Shields hang above the fireplace. They are likely still quite functional, despite serving a temporary decorative purpose. They bear patterns characteristic of Ysgardian culture.~
@300424 = ~This enormous skeleton of an unknown creature has been stripped of all flesh. Who, or what, slaughtered and devoured it remains a mystery.~
@300425 = ~Perhaps the greatest mystery of this place is this solitary gear. Did it come from the Ditch, or from some Ysgardian clock? Nothing nearby hints at its purpose.~
@300426 = ~The carcass of a large deer, stripped of most of its edible flesh. In Ysgard, all wildlife tends to be somewhat larger. Flies and scavenging vermin show a particular fondness for this corpse.~
@300427 = ~The gate you came through looks as if it was placed here deliberately, but also in haste. Without a doubt, it could be demolished with ease.~
@300428 = ~A lone, large tower stands at the shore of the frozen lake below.~
@300429 = ~This skull is far too large for any creature you've seen, yet it looks... almost human. It seems fused with the rock behind it.~
@300430 = ~A large city, built from what appears to be ice, looms over the frozen landscape. A tall citadel marks its center. This must be Mephistar.~
@300431 = ~A flag bearing the symbol of Mt. Celestia, one of the Upper Planes, flies above the field hospital. The symbol is easy to recognize: a triangle representing a mountain with a horizontal line crossing its peak.~
@300432 = ~Judging by the beds and all the medical equipment, including bandages, medications, and the like, it appears to be a field hospital. The sick lie under blankets, and the beds are speckled with blood, urine, and vomit. The smell is terrible, and even the fragrant oils someone has applied cannot mask it.~
@300435 = ~Above the symbol of a hand holding a lightning bolt, a monumental statue gazes down, emanating chivalry, justice, honor, valor, and courage. If it is a temple to some god, then despite its impressive scale, it appears lonely and abandoned.~
@300436 = ~The crude painting, meticulously drawn on the wall with white paint, depicts a Harmonium symbol hanging from a gallows.~
@300437 = ~"Is there life before death?"~
@300438 = ~The traveling salesman's wagon is filled to the brim with various crates and barrels containing his products. It teeters precariously close to the edge.~
@300439 = ~The Ditch deposits its most dense refuse in this small bay.~
@300440 = ~The lower floor of this house is completely flooded, but the water is slowly flowing to somewhere deeper.~
@300441 = ~This stair used to lead to another floor, but that floor is no more.~
@300442 = ~The yagnoloths must have been thorough. There's no way to reach the other side of this area from up here.~
@300443 = ~This container is filled with earth. It is unclear for what purpose.~
@300444 = ~Something large collapsed into the grotto from above, likely during the whole razorvine cataclysm.~
@300445 = ~An old boat. Wonder where it might have taken its owner before becoming trapped in this grotto.~
@300446 = ~A primitive-looking idol carved out of stone catches your eye. You think it somewhat resembles a face. It seems to be the focus of worship for the kuo-toa.~
@300447 = ~Among the posters, most of the space is taken up by missing-person notices. There is also an advertisement for a beach and a schedule of performances for the Beneathmask Theater.~
@300448 = ~This door has been boarded up from the inside.~
@300449 = ~You can't be certain, but the blackboard may be depicting the Inner Planes.~
@300450 = ~All that remains of the famous Fragile-Tail.~
@300451 = ~Whatever this animal was, it has been stripped clean of flesh, but the skeleton does not look very old.~
@300452 = ~Some kind of machine, half buried in trash and half submerged.~
@300453 = ~Just a short distance from the shore, a large clocktower leans in the water.~
@300454 = ~Someone once lived here.~
@300455 = ~A large and beautiful musical instrument.~
@300456 = ~These tools are all made of painted light wood and were likely used in one of the plays.~
@300457 = ~This is a sensory stone, but it looks fake.~
@300458 = ~It's a miracle that, for so many years, this precariously balanced pyramid of barrels hasn't collapsed, spilling its contents onto the forest floor.~
@300459 = ~A wild, primeval forest stretches all around the platform, as far as the eye can see.~
@300460 = ~Atop the steep wall, you can see Sigil's 'mainland.' No wonder you had to arrive here by raft.~
@300461 = ~A bright light shines from behind these bars... but there's no visible source. The hallway, like the alleyway, ends in a dead end.~
@300462 = ~These are the ruins of a once-majestic stairway.~
@300463 = ~A massive, rusty blade covered in razorvine protrudes from the water. It is a single solid piece of metal. The forge that produced this colossus must have been enormous.~
@300464 = ~The purpose of these devices is a mystery to you.~
@300465 = ~A massive valve. You cannot imagine what kind of creature it would take to operate it.~
@300466 = ~The entrance to the theater was barricaded from the inside. The tale of your betrayal must have reached the artists. You will need to return with more men to break through.~
@300467 = ~The theater chairs were turned into makeshift barricades, protecting the stage.~
@300468 = ~The Doomguard symbol painted in blood. It appears the raid did not go well for the defenders of the theater.~

