This item resembles a drop of blood with the consistency of a jelly bean. Consuming it distributes its healing power throughout the body.

The body charm surpasses not only the clot and blood charms but also the heart charm. It instantly heals wounds across the body and provides a surge of energy. It was created to treat injuries far more serious than those caused by bar fights or occasional dungeon excursions. Such charms are especially useful for planewalkers, for whom battling fiends or celestials is a real possibility.~
@500135 = ~Anulus Demonis~
@500136 = ~^NATTENTION: To unequip the ring, the Nameless One must NOT be holding a weapon, or the game will crash. Simply place one weapon in your inventory to free up a slot.^-

ANULUS DEMONIS

Transformation into a fiend can be frightening for some, but quite manageable or even enjoyable for others. For you, it could be useful in tricky situations and might even help scare off a stubborn opponent.

Jokes aside, there are several benefits to transforming into a Glabrezu. Strength, dexterity, and constitution are all significantly improved. Unfortunately, there are drawbacks as well. Once transformed, you will not be popular with ordinary mortals, many of whom will find your appearance abhorrent. You lose the ability to cast spells and experience constant anxiety, likely caused by the curse of being a fiend. On the bright side, you do feel much stronger.

Strength +3
Constitution +3
Dexterity +3
Charisma -5
Additional health points resulting from the increase of constitution.
Magic resistance: +16
Weight: 1

You cannot cast spells while in fiend form.
The curse remains active for the entire duration of the transformation.~
