This axe is made of iramant, a unique metal from Wrath's Deep, the 262nd layer of the Abyss. It was once claimed by a cambion lord, a self-proclaimed ruler of demons, but was abandoned after his sentencing to the Wells of Darkness. Today, his blacksmiths remain in the abyssal colony, still smelting magical weapons from the local ore.

Not all of the alleged facts surrounding Kabatum's trophy seem credible, but that matters little when you examine this magnificent weapon. Indeed, it would be wasted as a mere display piece. Whether iramant, extracted from the endless void, is a real material or not, contact with it incites greater ferocity in both enemies and the wielder, which can lead to a loss of touch with reality. Truly, madness lies dormant in the depths of the Abyss.

The righteous will have a hard time wielding this axe. It is intended for irredeemable sinners who display amoralism and hypocrisy, traits alien to the peaceful Upper Planes. Or so it seems.~
@500179 = ~Skin of Devils' Dread~
@500180 = ~SKIN OF DEVILS' DREAD
Invokes: "Horror" once a day
Weight: 10
 

This is a piece of skin from a hellchain weaver, a spider-beast from the darkest recesses of the Nine Hells, feared even by devils. Every creature in the Nine Hells recognizes the sound of these chains and can distinguish them from any torturer or penitent. That is what a hellchain weaver's skin is made of: cruel hooks, barbed chains, and jagged iron. Shake it hard, and its clanging will send shivers down even a baatezu's spine.

No matter how you hold this ghastly chain net, the tiny spikes and blades covering each link prick your fingers. When shaken, these sharp protrusions rub against each other, producing an unsettling rattle and grinding sound, almost as if it carries wails of despair and shrieks of agony. Some of the spikes seem to grasp the user's hand greedily, cutting the fingers.

When wielded, it creates an eerie rattle and grinding noise that instills fear in creatures within its field of vision.~
