Somehow, these bolts contain the power of the Quasi-Elemental Plane of Lightning, also called the Plane of Storms or, more poetically, the Vengeful Land. The only beings likely able to create such bolts and survive are the vrrxlzk, more commonly called shockers by planewalkers.

They are divided into two groups: the peaceful Contested Ones and the exploratory Sojourners who seek to leave their plane. Such bolts serve their purpose by sending lightning to places they could never reach without outside help.~
@500193 = ~Bolts of Primordial Rot~
@500194 = ~BOLTS OF PRIMORDIAL ROT
Damage: 2-5 (piercing)
Enchantment: +3
Special:
 5 magical cold damage on hit
Thac0: +2
Speed: 4
Weight: 0
Proficiency: Missiles
Can be used only by modrons

Many have discussed the cruel influence that the god of rot, corruption, and decay once had on the planes. Rumors about the slain god's remains include tales of bolts created to spread his decay, allowing his dark glory to return. Whether this is even possible remains a matter of debate, and there is no agreement about whether he was truly destroyed. These uncertainties are fitting for an evil deity who maintained control through lies and half truths. His tentacles were said to move through rotting matter, planting the seed of Moander in sleeping or paralyzed creatures and bringing with it a strange and unknown darkness.

The bolts bear the symbol of a hand with a fanged maw.~
@500195 = ~Bolts of Extending the Weave~
@500196 = ~BOLTS OF EXTENDING THE WEAVE
Damage: 2-5 (crushing)
Enchantment: +3
Special:
 5 magical damage on hit
Thac0: +2
Speed: 4
Weight: 0
Proficiency: Missiles
Can be used only by modrons

It is said that Mystryl gifted the races of the Prime Material Plane with magic. She later came to regret this gift. As wondrous as it was, many evil mages exploited it and twisted it to the limits of their corrupted imaginations. In doing so, they created successive generations of power hungry tyrants who sought to cheat both life and death.

Magic has clearly shaped not only its practitioners but also ordinary people. One result was the rise of a vast market for magical potions and enchanted items. These bolts embody the idea of expanding the Weave, the source of raw magic from which spellcasters draw their power. The Weave flows through nearly every place except dead magic zones. Where it is thin or absent, spellcasting becomes far more difficult, as on Abeir. The Weave is also structured differently on various planes, which alters the way spells function. Any mage who has tried to increase their power in Carceri has noticed this. So has any telepath who hears the whispers of eavesdropping devils in Avernus, not to mention the strange transformation of Bigby's Crushing Hand, which can manifest fiendish claws there.

Even if understanding the true nature of the Weave remains difficult, perhaps impossible, using it in combat is well within reach. Beyond the battlefield, these projectiles are meant to extend the network of the Weave and strengthen the presence of magic in regions where it has not yet taken hold. If the Weave were ever to collapse, it would likely unleash a catastrophe unlike anything the planes have ever known.~
@500197 = ~Jade Skull~
@500198 = ~JADE SKULL
Weight: 2

A miniature skull carved from a precious stone. It appears to serve no purpose other than perhaps acting as a striking yet grotesque paperweight.~
@500199 = ~Can Ghosts Bleed?~
@500200 = ~CAN GHOSTS BLEED?
Weight: 1

This volume, written by an anonymous member or group of members of the Athar, explores whether living beings truly possess souls and what that might imply. A paragraph highlighted in charcoal by a previous reader catches your eye. It reads:

"They say that in the heavens of the Upper Planes we are fulfilled. But what about memories? How can a person burdened by trauma and nightmarish experiences feel eternal joy in paradise? Does the spirit shed them in some form of purgatory, or in heaven itself? And if so, is it still fulfilled after losing its memories? Is it still truly itself without the experiences of life? After all, trauma and regret are inevitable parts of experience, and without them the spirit is no longer the same person it was in life. So can eternal life, which is meant to be paradise, become a trap with no escape for those whose mortal lives were filled with suffering and madness? For such people, would it not be better to die forever in the full sense of the word than to lose themselves or become trapped in a paradise that turns into a personal hell?"

Similar arguments and counterarguments to common religious beliefs appear throughout the book, clearly expressing the author's opposition to an afterlife imposed by the gods.
~
@500201 = ~The Paths of Destiny~
@500202 = ~THE PATHS OF DESTINY
Weight: 1

This book is a collection of short stories that explore the inevitability of fate and destiny. Some are blissful, while others are overwhelming. The moment it lands in your hands, the bookmark marks the beginning of the following untitled story:

"Once upon a time, in an inaccessible realm, there lived a peaceful and gentle people who cared nothing for the shadow of war that hung over them. It was not their war, they said. When the conflict finally fell upon them like a cataclysm, weeping and gnashing of teeth soon followed.

Among them stood a strange warrior whom they had welcomed when misfortune first came upon them. He roused them from their passivity. His zeal and faith awakened their anger and courage and showed them how strong they could be. Inspired by his example, they went to war to defend their homes and families. The blessing given to the warrior by his beloved stirred their hearts, and an angel proclaimed their victory. As they marched toward glory, none of them realized that the warrior who led them was not driven by care or love, but by a sickness that his surroundings had long restrained, until at last he passed it on to them all.

Faith and courage brought them success. They triumphed and proved their strength. Yet when they returned home, they found only tragedy and ruin. When their proud leader saw the body of his beloved, he understood that if he had not given in to his illness, they might have remained home and protected those they loved. But it was too late. He was left alone, exposed to the full force of the sickness he had once tried to turn against his enemies, and he became its victim in the worst possible way.

Consumed by grief and guilt, the great warrior took his own life. He went to war once more, this time alone and leaving nothing behind. He declared war on an overwhelming force and fell beneath the onslaught of his enemies, hoping that with his death his misery would finally end.

He sought rest in death, but it was not granted to him. He had never understood that his illness was not part of his life but part of his own soul. In the world of the dead, there is no escape from oneself."~
@500203 = ~Priestess's Note~
@500204 = ~PRIESTESS'S NOTE
Weight: 0

This short note was written by a priestess who left the package at the port warehouse. It is written in a language you do not recognize, but three words resemble those in Common:

"water," "belief," "chance"~
@500205 = ~A Coin with a Two-Faced Likeness~
@500206 = ~Greater Coin of Fate~
@500207 = ~A COIN WITH A TWO-FACED LIKENESS 
Weight: 0

Both sides of this coin show an almost identical image of two female faces fused together. Both are beautiful, but one conveys peace while the other appears malicious. One side is a mirror image of the other.~
@500208 = ~GREATER COIN OF FATE
Weight: 0

Sometimes life and death are decided by the toss of a coin.

Both sides of this coin show an almost identical image of two female faces fused together. Both are beautiful, but one conveys peace while the other appears malicious. One side is a mirror image of the other. You recognize the two goddesses of fate in these women: Tymora and Beshaba.

When you toss this coin, the outcome can go one of two ways: everything may feel a little easier for a moment, or quite the opposite. You can never be certain of the result.~
@500209 = ~Searing Axe~
@500210 = ~Axe of Ragnarök~
@500211 = ~SEARING AXE
Damage: 3-18 Slashing
Speed: 3
Weight: 5
Proficiency: Edged
Can be used only by Fighters.

This axe is so hot to the touch that you instinctively pull your hand back. It is difficult to explain how it does not burn everything nearby.~
@500212 = ~AXE OF RAGNARÖK
Damage: 3-18 Slashing
Enchanted: +3
Special:
 +2 to Armor Class
 +20 Magical Fire Damage
 +20% Resistance to Fire and Magical Fire
 +20% Resistance to Magical Fire
THAC0: +2
Speed: 3
Weight: 5
Proficiency: Edged
Can be used only by Fighters.

Surtur, the lord of the fire giants of Muspelheim, is destined to scorch the world one day during Ragnarök, the Twilight of the Gods. No weapon can match his sun-bright sword, but the temples of Mannheim hold many secrets. Among them are vast armaments designed to prepare the giants and their allies for the coming end.~
@500213 = ~Freezing Axe~
@500214 = ~Axe of Ultimate Despair~
@500215 = ~FREEZING AXE
Damage: 3-18 Slashing
Speed: 4
Weight: 5
Proficiency: Edged
Can be used only by Fighters.

This axe is extremely cold to the touch, so much so that you can see vapor rising from it.~
@500216 = ~AXE OF ULTIMATE DESPAIR
Damage: 3-18 Slashing
Enchanted: +3
Special:
 +2 to Armor Class
 +20 Magical Cold Damage
 +20% Resistance to Cold and Magical Cold
THAC0: +3
Speed: 4
Weight: 5
Proficiency: Edged
Can be used only by Fighters.

Yggdrasil stretches far, even reaching Hades. Here lies Niflheim, the Northmen's Despair, the land where the evil death goddess Hel is imprisoned. The cold produces a constant, chilling fog that soaks clothing and rusts metal at an alarming rate. This power is bound to an axe that emits a vaporous fog, difficult to overcome even for powerful foes, while making the wielder resistant to the cold.~
@500217 = ~Smelly Old Axe~
@500218 = ~Rotting Axe of Corruption~
@500219 = ~SMELLY OLD AXE
Damage: 3-18 Slashing
Speed: 4
Weight: 5
Proficiency: Edged
Can be used only by Fighters.

The smell of this old axe is unpleasant and hard to bear. It appears rusty and worn, and it is difficult to tell if it will be of any use.~
@500220 = ~ROTTING AXE OF CORRUPTION
Damage: 3-18 Slashing
Enchanted: +2
Special:
 Poisons the opponent
 +2 to Armor Class
 +20 Acid Damage
 +20% Resistance to Acid
 Immunity to Poison
 +2 Save vs. Death
THAC0: +2
Speed: 4
Weight: 5
Proficiency: Edged
Can be used only by Fighters.

The toll of the followers of Moander, the Bringer of Darkness, is unimaginable. Weapons touched by their fragments retain lethal properties for centuries, and those struck by them die in excruciating pain. This axe is set with a stone engraved with the symbol of a hand bearing an open, fanged mouth, a reminder of the millennia-long struggle for the ultimate dissolution of the multiverse.~
@500221 = ~Electrified Axe~
@500222 = ~Wind Axe of Aaqa~
@500223 = ~ELECTRIFIED AXE
Damage: 3-18 Slashing
Speed: 2
Weight: 5
Proficiency: Edged
Can be used only by Fighters.

When you bring your hand close to it, you feel the hairs on your back rise and see them standing on end. There is something about this weapon that sends a shiver down your spine every time you touch it.~
@500224 = ~WIND AXE OF AAQA
Damage: 3-18 Slashing
Enchanted: +2
Special:
 +2 to Armor Class
 +20 Fire Damage
 +20% Resistance to Electricity
THAC0: +1
Speed: 2
Weight: 5
Proficiency: Edged
Can be used only by Fighters.
Cannot be used by Chaotic characters.

This axe originally belonged to the vault of the vaati, the Wind Dukes of Aaqa in the Elemental Plane of Air. It may have begun its journey through the planes during the war against the Queen of Chaos, one of the obyriths, ancient demons of the Abyss. The Wind Dukes represented Law, so the battle was fierce, especially when the Queen raised a general, Miska the Wolf-Spider, the predecessor of the infamous Demogorgon. Miska's army conquered world after world. While the Dukes' elite, the Captains of Law, focused on crafting a powerful artifact called the Rod of Law, ordinary soldiers needed weapons capable of standing against the greater tanar'ri. Axes like this one were imbued with lightning energy, incredibly fast, and deadly against fiends. Today it remains a souvenir of a fallen empire.~
@500225 = ~Cerebral Parasite Earring~
@500226 = ~CEREBRAL PARASITE EARRING
Special:
 +3 to Intelligence
 +1 to Wisdom
 -1 to Constitution
 Immunity to Panic
Weight: 1

One of the earrings Beatha makes from cerebral parasites called kassegs. They resemble intellect devourers but are much smaller. This would be unsurprising if not for the fact that a kasseg cannot survive more than a few hours after attaching itself to a host, having formed a mental bond. Miraculously, Beatha has made the benefits of this strange symbiosis permanent. The cost, beyond the considerable strain on the body, remains unknown to the wearer and most likely even to Beatha herself.~
@500227 = ~Clockroach Earring~
@500228 = ~CLOCKROACH EARRING
Special:
 +2 to Armor Class
 +2 to Armor Class vs. Crushing Attacks
 +10% Resistance vs. Crushing Attacks
 +10% Resistance vs. Acid
Weight: 2

This earring was crafted by Beatha from a miniature clockroach, a construct resembling a cockroach. These creatures were once released into the jungles of Chult to clear paths to ancient ruins, but now they consume not only garbage but also flora, artifacts, and unwary travelers. Normally the size of a dog, their sharp pincers and corrosive acid make them far more dangerous than their size suggests. Above all, they perfect a trait for which cockroaches are infamous: they are extremely difficult to kill. The earring allows you to magically acquire some of the traits of this relentless automaton.

Its effect is similar to that of a cockroach charm, but slightly weaker and permanent while worn. This is not merely a decorative trinket.~
@500229 = ~Frog Figurine~
@500230 = ~Figurine of Wondrous Power: Frog~
@500231 = ~FROG FIGURINE
Weight: 2

This life-size sculpture resembles a frog. It must have taken great skill to create with such precision, but it is unclear if it serves any purpose beyond artistic expression.~
@500232 = ~FIGURINE OF WONDROUS POWER: FROG
Special:
 Immunity to Poison
 +2 to Armor Class
 +2 Save vs. Breath
Weight: 2
Cannot be used by characters that are armless or burning

This life-size sculpture resembles a frog. Figurines of wondrous power are typically used to summon a sentient animal by placing them on the ground and speaking a command word. This one, however, has been modified by Beatha to grant the user the benefits of frog-like abilities while it is held. These benefits include improved camouflage, which enhances Armor Class, resistance to poison, and the ability to hold one's breath for an extended period.~
@500233 = ~Serpent Skin Wallet~
@500234 = ~SERPENT SKIN WALLET
Weight: 1

This wallet, likely made from the skin of a Shadow Sea serpent, is designed to store jewelry. Considering how popular jewelry is in Sigil, it could be a worthwhile purchase for better inventory management.

The unnatural properties of its material make the owner more difficult to rob. A thief might hesitate before reaching into the wallet's bottomless darkness. Its origin is the Shadowfell, the Plane of Shadow, where the Shades breed eldritch monstrosities, including enormous serpents crossed with whales that devour anything in their path. The enchantment on this wallet ensures that the owner can recover their possessions with ease, though some doubt is understandable.~
@500235 = ~Earring of a Tormented Soul~
@500236 = ~EARRING OF A TORMENTED SOUL
Special:
 Increases regeneration
 +5 to Health Points
 +2 Save vs. Death
 +1 to Armor Class
 -1 to Charisma
Weight: 1

The symbol tattooed on your arm has haunted you for an incomprehensible amount of time. Did it exist before, or was it born from Ravel's twisted magic? In any case, torment proves to be a force that, like magnetism, draws other tormented souls, and the weapon created by Coaxmetal took the same shape. Therefore, it should be possible to wear this symbol as an earring and use it to prepare the body for the pain to come. Still, expressing suffering does little to aid conversation.~
@500237 = ~Blood Fly Charm (Troll)~
@500238 = ~BLOOD FLY CHARM (TROLL)
Special:
 Heals 30 Hit Points
 Increases Regeneration
 -50% resistance to fire
Weight: 0

Blood flies are pests thought to have originated from one of the Lower Planes. In many ways, they resemble mosquitoes with an insatiable hunger. A cloud of blood flies can drain all the blood from a human body within minutes, and their stingers are capable of piercing even the skin of fiends.

Some healers use blood flies to draw diseased blood from a patient. Occasionally, swarms are employed to siphon rare types of blood. The flies are then paralyzed with powders or spells and stored for future use.

This particular blood fly charm appears to contain troll blood within its food sac. When the paralyzed fly is consumed, it immediately restores a small amount of damage and grants the user the ability to regenerate for a limited period. If the character already has the ability to regenerate, the effect increases the regeneration rate.~
@500239 = ~Blood Fly Charm (Cornugon)~
@500240 = ~BLOOD FLY CHARM (CORNUGON)
Special:
 Heals 50 Hit Points
 Increases Regeneration
 +10% resistance to fire
 +7% resistance to magical fire
 +3% resistance to magic
 Weight: 0

Blood flies are pests thought to have originated from one of the Lower Planes. In many ways, they resemble mosquitoes with an insatiable hunger. A cloud of blood flies can drain all the blood from a human body within minutes, and their stingers are capable of piercing even the skin of fiends.

Some healers use blood flies to draw diseased blood from a patient. Occasionally, swarms are employed to siphon rare types of blood. The flies are then paralyzed with powders or spells and stored for future use.

This particular blood fly charm appears to contain the blood of a greater fiend, a cornugon. These fiends are the elite of Baator's defenses, with some reporting directly to the Dark Eight. They can survive in extremely harsh conditions and mostly dwell in the lower circles of the Nine Hells. Yet even they bleed.~
@500241 = ~Blood Fly Charm (Gelugon)~
@500242 = ~BLOOD FLY CHARM (GELUGON)
Special:
 Heals 75 Hit Points
 Increases Regeneration
 +10% resistance to cold
 +7% resistance to magical cold
 +5% resistance to magic
 Weight: 0

Blood flies are pests thought to have originated from one of the Lower Planes. In many ways, they resemble mosquitoes with an insatiable hunger. A cloud of blood flies can drain all the blood from a human body within minutes, and their stingers are capable of piercing even the skin of fiends.

Some healers use blood flies to draw diseased blood from a patient. Occasionally, swarms are employed to siphon rare types of blood. The flies are then paralyzed with powders or spells and stored for future use.

This particular blood fly charm appears to contain the blood of an ice devil, a gelugon. Gelugons are insectoid guardians of Cania, the eighth layer of Baator.~
@500243 = ~Mint Earring~
@500244 = ~MINT EARRING
Special:
 +1 to Armor Class
 +3 to Charisma
 +10% resistance to cold
Weight: 1

This earring was crafted by Beatha from a piece of mint candy and clings to the ear like a pearl. The concept was simple, but the challenge lay in making the earring a durable piece of jewelry that could withstand varying weather conditions. The solution, perfectly suited to its refreshing mint scent, was a chill spell. The earring protects the wearer from cold and enhances their Charisma, ensuring that any conversation goes in their favor.~
@500245 = ~Mysterious Bag~
@500246 = ~MYSTERIOUS BAG
Weight: 1

This is a bag you purchased from the warehouse manager. Its contents are unknown.~
@500247 = ~Jade Jaw~
@500248 = ~JADE JAW
Weight: 1

A jawbone carved from precious stone. It is small, yet its shape closely resembles a human bone.~
@500249 = ~Clothes~
@500250 = ~CLOTHES
Weight: 1

Neatly folded clothes purchased at a Ditch marketplace. They once belonged to the naive young man who was robbed by a woman in a red dress.~
@500251 = ~SACRED SIGIL OF KNOWING
(Greater artifact)
 Special:
 Blur
 Improves Armor Class by 3
 Improves Strength by 1
 Improves Saving Throws
Weight: 0

This is the sacred signet ring that once belonged to the Word Archon of the Glass Tarn. It rested on a pedestal, for no one takes such precautions with ordinary jewelry. Inscribed upon it are brief fragments of the Metatext, records that unite all the knowledge of the Multiverse and grant access to its deepest secrets. These inscriptions are said to be the work of priests and monks of the Church of Deneir, known as glyphoscribes. The First Scribe of Oghma recorded and mastered the knowledge of the Metatext, and in doing so transcended reality.

The wisdom contained within empowers the wearer in ways otherwise unattainable. It allows them to partially step beyond this dimension of understanding, producing an effect akin to a permanent Blur spell. This makes the wearer much harder to strike while enabling them to tap into the hidden powers of the multiverse.

Once the truth is known, there is no return to the state of ignorance.~
@500252 = ~The Prophetess of Action~
@500253 = ~THE PROPHETESS OF ACTION
Weight: 1

This legendary work, written in prose, resembles an epic chivalric romance in form, but its content serves more as a mockery of the genre's ideals than as an example of them. Its author was the spirited spellscale priest Qafzech de Vermilion. The book is dedicated to the life and work of Celosia, a prophetess and saint of the cult of Garyx, the dragon god of fire and destruction. Unlike most clergy, Celosia, gifted in magic, preferred to demonstrate her faith through action rather than words. She became known as the Prophetess of Action. Described as a half-nymph, half-lizard woman of hellfire, she was said to be so austere in beauty that even her own god was enchanted. The work emphasizes the solemnity of the scenes of doom and desolation wrought by the protagonist during her pilgrimage. It glorifies acts of mass destruction and imbues them with a twisted significance.

This reissue was published by the Doomguard faction as recommended reading for the Sinkers, providing a literary introduction to their philosophy of destruction. To facilitate understanding, this edition features a detailed foreword by Taranis the Half-Dragon, who explains the parallels between Garyx's religion and the Doomguard's worldview.

"(...) Garyx is called the All-Destroyer, for his will can truly affect any object in the Great Wheel. A mortal's life, a magical artifact, a city, a deity, or even an entire plane may fall under his influence. Yet it is not Garyx but Faluzure and Chronepsis who are the dragons' gods of death. Garyx, venerated by the Doomguard, represents meaningful destruction. What is the meaning of destruction? This book seeks to answer that question.

Everything in the universe ages. Everything will one day pass away. Although Garyx and this book claim that dragonkind is eternal, one must accept the truth that dragons will also eventually become extinct. Celosia explains the meaning of this, the beauty of doom. After destruction comes renewal, like a burned forest that regrows. Extinction crowns decay and decadence just as death ends old age and disease. Readers may find many interpretations within this work, but all lead to the common goal of the Doomguard and the cult of the All-Destroyer, completion.

Some remove the rot from the world and replace it with new, more beautiful life. Others revel in destruction and leave the resulting void to fate. Destruction can have countless motivations, just as Saint Celosia's actions can be interpreted in different ways, revenge, wrath, or mercy. Every act of destruction has meaning. It is for this purpose that the Doomguard reissues this work, not necessarily to celebrate Garyx personally or to foster his cult, as the original author intended, but above all to demonstrate the beauty and ecstasy of destruction. Faith in the Cleanser of Worlds, personally professed and recommended by the initiator of this edition and author of its foreword, is a welcome addition but not required to appreciate the prose or emulate its lessons. Reader, read it with a flushed face and allow yourself to be carried along by the conflagration engulfing the Great Wheel. May the Prophetess of Action ignite your passion and guide your purpose through destruction. Let her lead you in the dance of doomsday. (...)"

In this copy of the book, the most striking moment is the baptism of fire, in which the protagonist becomes an avatar of her god and unleashes a fiery storm upon her family grove. The descriptions of Garyx and Celosia's reunion at the center of the conflagration, combined with the depiction of the fire god's presence in the flames consuming the naked body of the heroine, are suggestive. They give the impression that, in that moment, their union was driven by something more mundane than divine incarnation, yet no less intense than the ecstasy of pyromania.~
@500254 = ~A Bleaker's Manifesto~
@500255 = ~A BLEAKER'S MANIFESTO
Weight: 1

This is an unofficial set of rules written by Ími of the Bleak Cabal, intended to summarize the beliefs and reflections of this faction.

1. I do not seek meaning in all this, for knowing the world is impossible and should remain so. The only meaning I can find is meaninglessness.

2. I worship no deities. They are nothing more than powerful mortals whom Entropy will eventually claim, and their priests likely spread lies.

3. There are no absolute truths, and no one has ever known them nor will they ever know them. Perception of the world is subjective.

4. This life is the only one we have. I do not trust those who promise life after death, freedom from evil spirits, or divine blessings in exchange for temple donations.

5. True freedom comes from inner peace and faithfulness to oneself, for only within can any semblance of meaning be found.

6. I do not allow myself to be hypocritical or foolish, traits so often found in the members and leaders of other groups.

7. I dare to doubt. Everything that has been written may be false, including this text.

8. I accept reality as it is, but I oppose those who impose their will on those who have not formed their own.

9. The value of everything, including my own life, is subjective and depends on perspective.

10. I accept that all must die. When the time comes, every stone will be crushed.~
@500256 = ~Bone of Thanatos~
@500257 = ~BONE OF THANATOS
Weight: 1
Can be used only by The Nameless One

A gift for a new acolyte of Kiaransalee.

"... and as the White Banshee reveled in the fruits of her work, her wasteful consort, ruled by the illusions of vanity, grew ever more resentful to his once beloved. And as the White Banshee strove to beat death itself and reverse the natural order of things, the wasteful consort was bent on moving tiny pawns of irrelevancy on his tiny, pitiful board. 

Alas, the many small have drowned out the voice of greatest one in the end, and the White Banshee was cast down, disowned, her kingdom not her own any more, even when she dedicated herself in her entirety for the good of her people. 

The White Banshee looked up from the depths of her imprisonment, and the White Banshee saw that the kingdom rejoiced under the consort's trivialities. Their minds and spirits grew weak, insignificant, unworthy of their former queen's love. 

The White Banshee then knew she erred in her ways and would set her eyes on righting this wrong. She would bring meaningful death to this world of meaningless life..." ~
@500258 = ~The History of Interfactional Diplomacy~
@500259 = ~THE HISTORY OF INTERFACTIONAL DIPLOMACY
Weight: 1

This book explores the nuances of the complex relationships between factions and the history of diplomacy, giving considerable attention to alliances and conflicts among them. Countless factions have emerged over the years. Some that were once significant have fallen or been replaced, while others remain small sects that, despite their limited membership, often prove a persistent thorn in the side of larger groups. At the time of writing, fifteen factions are officially recognized, making it a daunting task to memorize all their relationships. These connections are not symmetrical and can only be understood in a general, intuitive sense. Each faction is based on different planes, both Outer and Inner, but they are most likely to encounter one another in the middle, in the City of Doors, Sigil.

An important conclusion drawn from this work is that factions with similar views will tend to cooperate, while those with opposing philosophies are likely to become hostile. As a result, projects that require cooperation among multiple factions must take into account their respective alignments and animosities.

Below are some of the more important interfactional relationships to consider:

Athar
Factol: Terrance
Allies: Believers of the Source (good relations and frequent cooperation, shared belief in rising above the powers)
Enemies: Doomguard (criticism of the extreme methods of their factol, Pentar)

Believers of the Source
Factol: Ambar Vergrove
Allies: Athar (good relations), Doomguard (shared belief in the ultimate end of the multiverse)
Enemies: Dustmen, Bleak Cabal (disagreements of opinion)

Bleak Cabal
Factol: Lhar
Allies: Doomguard, Dustmen, Revolutionary League, Xaositects
Enemies: Fraternity of Order, Harmonium, Mercykillers (lawful beings cannot accept the Bleak Cabal philosophy), Sign of One (responsible for the death of a former factol)

Doomguard
Factol: Pentar
Allies: Dustmen, Believers of the Source, Bleak Cabal, Xaositects (shared belief in entropy)
Enemies: Fraternity of Order, Harmonium (opposed to entropy)

Dustmen
Factol: Skall
Allies: Bleak Cabal, Doomguard, Fated, Lords of the Undead (Dead Truce)
Enemies: Society of Sensation, Sign of One (opposed to Dustmen fatalism)

Fated
Factol: Rowan Darkwood
Allies: Free League (shared views on independence), Mercykillers (opposition to mercy, adherence to the law of the strongest)
Enemies: Harmonium (closely monitored by them)

Fraternity of Order
Factol: Hashkar
Allies: Mercykillers, Harmonium (joint enforcement of the law and administration of justice in Sigil)
Enemies: Xaositects, Revolutionary League (antithetical to the orderly principles of the Guvners)

Free League
Factol: none
Allies: Fated (shared views on independence)
Enemies: Harmonium (perceived as overly suspicious and hostile to freedom)

Harmonium
Factol: Sarin
Allies: Fraternity of Order, Mercykillers (joint enforcement of the law and administration of justice in Sigil)
Enemies: Fated, Revolutionary League, Xaositects (considered criminal or suspect), Transcendent Order (disagreement over the concept of order)

Mercykillers
Factol: Alisohn Nilesia
Allies: Harmonium, Fraternity of Order, Doomguard, Fated (adherence to the law of the strongest, opposition to mercy)
Enemies: Revolutionary League, Society of Sensation, Sign of One (frequent legal conflicts)

Revolutionary League
Factol: none
Allies: Doomguard, Xaositects (support the disintegration of existing order)
Enemies: Harmonium, Mercykillers, Fraternity of Order (represent the structures anarchists oppose)

Sign of One
Factol: Darius
Allies: Society of Sensation (similar beliefs)
Enemies: Harmonium, Bleak Cabal (conflicting views)

Society of Sensation
Factol: Erin Darkflame Montgomery
Allies: Sign of One (shared approach to egoism), Fraternity of Order, Free League (mutual respect through the pursuit of knowledge)
Enemies: Doomguard (philosophical differences)

Transcendent Order
Factol: Rhys
Allies: Most factions (disinterested in actual alliances or conflicts)
Enemies: Harmonium (disagreement over the concept of order)

Xaositects
Factol: Karan
Allies: Doomguard, Bleak Cabal (aligned by chaos)
Enemies: Harmonium, Fraternity of Order (opposed to chaos)

The book concludes with a comprehensive set of footnotes and references to other political, historical, and legal publications in multiple languages.~
@500260 = ~Limbo in Limbo~
@500261 = ~LIMBO IN LIMBO
Weight: 1

FOREWORD
by Kieran the planewalker

"Hello, my friend! If you are reading these words, it means you are curious about the multiverse and its planes, and that makes you my kindred spirit. With a clear conscience, I can call you my friend.

So, my friend, I invite you on another of my journeys along the Great Wheel. This time, I have wandered into a place with a rather bad reputation. Wrong! I have heard so much about how terrible and unfriendly Limbo is, but it is simply not true. I will show you in the pages of this book that a positive attitude opens all doors and sometimes even creates them out of thin air.

We will stroll along the impressive gray streets of Shra'kt'lor with the delightfully friendly githzerai. I will teach you how to swim in pure chaos, harnessing the power of positive thinking. Then we will take a break at Barnstable, enjoy slaad stew, and sing traditional halfling chants with the hosts. Finally, we will visit Fenmarel Mestarine's domain. I tried to convince him of the power of friendship, but I do not think he was ready to accept love into his heart yet. Perhaps you will be luckier than I was.

Now, let us embark on this magical journey through the Multiverse without delay and discover all the wonders it has to offer. It is so beautiful, after all. If you just smile at it, it will smile back at you.

Kieran"

Beneath the signature is a simple drawing of a smiling face with angel wings and a halo.~
@500262 = ~By Torch and Shield: A Guide to the Elemental Plane of Fire~
@500263 = ~"BY TORCH AND SHIELD: A GUIDE TO THE ELEMENTAL PLANE OF FIRE"
Weight: 1

FOREWORD
by Kieran the planewalker

"I would like to extend a welcome to you, my traveling companion through the planes. Perhaps I should say a warm welcome, for today I plan to take you to the warmest place in the entire multiverse, the Elemental Plane of Fire.

It is undoubtedly an extraordinary place, full of people with warm hearts, unique monuments, and natural wonders you will not see anywhere else. I recommend bringing cold drinks, a good moisturizer, and plenty of smiles. A flame-proof potion will also be useful if you plan to explore the trackless wilderness of this plane, or you may end up as a pile of ash.

If you prefer reading to walking, and basking by a fireplace sounds better than swimming in white heat, do not worry. In the following pages, I will tell you about the most fascinating things the Elemental Plane of Fire has to offer. We will haggle amicably with the azers in the Crucible's marketplace, visit the beautiful mosques of the City of Brass, and finally explore the Citadel of Fire, which shares a long and colorful history with the City of Doors. Everything in the Multiverse is connected.

Now, I invite you on a journey that will warm your bones and ignite passion in your heart. Onward to adventure.

Kieran"

Beneath the signature is a simple drawing of a smiling face with angel wings and a halo.~
@500264 = ~~
@500265 = ~SHINA-TSU-HIKO MILK
Weight: 1

The label is marked with three curly lines. Could it be real milk inside? Perhaps it is the milk of that creature called Shina-Tsu-Hiko, a name that sounds strange to your ears. It is difficult to answer these questions, and the effects of this cloudy, white, slightly bitter drink on anyone who consumes the contents of the small bottle remain unclear.~
@500266 = ~~
@500268 = ~A Piece of String Covered in Saliva~
@500269 = ~A PIECE OF STRING COVERED IN SALIVA
Weight: 1

A short piece of string, cut evenly at both ends. It appears to be of fairly good quality despite its pitiful, slobbery condition. The string is soaked in some kind of grease, likely intended to make it waterproof. The coating also made it appealing to the kuo-toa who once possessed it.~
@500270 = ~A Note from the Priestess of Istishia~
@500271 = ~A NOTE FROM THE PRIESTESS OF ISTISHIA
Weight: 0

Whoever you are, read this. I was here, Aquafina the cleric, trying to convert a bunch of stubborn kuo-toa to the only true faith of Istishia, but they just would not listen. They started to profess it, but they still make bloody sacrifices to him now, and somehow I feel like I have become the leader of this cult. I am sure some Mercykillers will come eventually and feed ME to their wyrm for all of this.

So I decided to slip away quietly.

If you are a representative of the law in Sigil: the kuo-toa are down there, I recommend violence, I am innocent.

If you are an adventurer: the kuo-toa are down there, I recommend violence.

If you are some kid snooping around in basements: RUN!~
@500272 = ~Toxic Drink~
@500273 = ~TOXIC DRINK
Weight: 1

The poisonous green color of this drink is clearly suspicious. Simply approaching the container makes you feel nauseous. Opening it is probably unwise unless you know how to handle it. Perhaps the marilith bartender intended to serve it to one of the guests.~
@500274 = ~Vudran Water~
@500275 = ~VUDRAN WATER
Invokes: "Adder's Kiss" on three targets at once, once a day
Weight: 1
Cannot be used by Good characters

The 531st layer of the Abyss, Vudra, is known for its highly toxic air and its blood ocean. It is ruled by the marilith queen Shaktari, who was captured by some of the Baatorian Lords of the Nine and taken to the Wells of Darkness, then released by an unknown baernaloth to incite the Blood War. Whether the marilith bartender intended to poison any of the guests remains a mystery. It is unlikely that she spared him out of sentimental attachment to her family plane.

Toxic water vapors will reach their targets if the container is properly aimed after opening. The effect should last for a considerable time, dealing 2 to 8 points of damage to three targets every five seconds. The duration is extended as if the user were an 18th-level mage.~
@500276 = ~Big Bone~
@500277 = ~BIG BONE
Weight: 2

The bone that, for some unknown reason, once belonged to Agraval. It appears to be human.~
@500278 = ~Bone of Lies~
@500279 = ~BONE OF LIES
Invokes: "Reign of Anger" on three targets at once, once a day
Weight: 2
Cannot be used by Good characters

Portent in Gehenna is a treacherous place, filled with murder and lies. A tiefling oracle named Laughing Jane lives there, with snakes writhing from her empty eyes, each mouth speaking a different word. Somewhere within her speech lies the truth, but what does it matter when it cannot be verified?

Jane's words were enchanted into this bone, which once belonged to one of Gehenna's petitioners. It can be used as a wand capable of weaponizing words. To activate it, one must select exactly three targets. They will be struck by up to five missiles, each dealing 3 to 6 points of damage.~
@500280 = ~Heavy Flail~
@500281 = ~HEAVY FLAIL
Damage: 1-10, crushing
Speed: 2
Weight: 20
Proficiency: Clubs
Unusable by Mages

A black, spiked bar made of a cold material resembling bone, and studded with twelve studs, is attached to the handle.~
@500282 = ~Devil's Bane~
@500283 = ~DEVIL'S BANE
Damage: 1-10, crushing
Enchanted: +3
Special:
 +2 Armor Class
THAC0: +2
Speed: 3
Weight: 20
Proficiency: Clubs
Unusable by Mages

This is a weapon that Valen the weapon master has come to favor. It is a heavy flail. A black, spiked bar made of a cold material resembling bone, studded with twelve studs, is attached to the handle. These heads increase its striking power, setting it apart from the simple flails used by farmers. Its drawback is a lack of precision, but it is highly effective at breaking through enemy defences. In Valen's case, a veteran of the Blood War, those enemies were hordes of fiends. As a result, the weapon was inevitably shaped for that purpose.~
@500284 = ~Empyrean Diamond~
@500285 = ~EMPYREAN DIAMOND
Weight: 0

A flawless, radiant gemstone that emits a soft, divine light. It is said to be extremely valuable.~
@500286 = ~Rope~
@500287 = ~ROPE
Weight: 3

Around 30 feet of strong, thick rope.~
@500288 = ~Worse to Ask the Way than to Go Astray~
@500289 = ~WORSE TO ASK THE WAY THAN TO GO ASTRAY
Weight: 1

"I, one of many who have fallen, clinging desperately to life and poisoned, write this warning for all the greedy and utterly foolish, for you who walk the paths of ignorance.

Heed the signs, for the hour has struck and there is no turning back.

*

It would seem that the angels seek nothing.

He sought knowledge, but also a paradise long lost, like sand that so often slips through one's fingers.

There was a time when I myself searched for I know not what. At last, my wish was granted, and the Abyss appeared in empty eyes, a gaze behind which a vortex of confusion hides.

I soon realized it was not I who was asking the questions, but the questions that were being asked of me.

One morning, he arrived in the splendor of his fallen glory, all his boundless majesty founded upon pillars of power that elude ordinary perception and a beauty that cannot be fully seen. How hypocritical it all was. He presented himself as a "friend."

Promises, real miracles, solved tasks, all these things I had. And finally, convinced of my own divinity, my twisted mind sought the path to ultimate perfection: immortality. But I know now this is merely a reflection of true death in the distorting mirror of a haunted, false life.

And so, passing through successive levels of knowledge, I arrived at the universal crime. He told me, in a whisper: "Murder is equal to the gift of life. Does not everything perish so that the new may be born? Does not the young consume the old?" And sometimes I still hear that voice. I have fallen into the mirror image of doom, and I know I have forgotten the way to my old home.

Perhaps we revel in the glory of our own anomalous lives, only to find our journey insignificant.

Or perhaps we are the perfect angels.

The "friend" will explain everything to you, taking only your soul in return."~
@500290 = ~Manifesto?~
@500291 = ~MANIFESTO?
Weight: 0

"To the free people of this world!


Verily, nothing stranger could occur to a simple and hackneyed mind like mine than to think of carping at the rulers. And yet it happened, for appearances are deceptive.

The situation is not rosy. The rulers are devoid of honor, although power creates the illusion that honor should always come first for such a person. I will point out at once that, as in every pathology, there are exceptions. However, in general, rulers are cunning individuals who believe that everything is theirs and that they are entitled to everything. This cunning stems from the fact that, thanks to their superior position, they think they can deceive our simple minds. But truly, does not life teach us that wisdom and intelligence are two different attributes?

Their haughty manners, evasive speech, expensive clothes, and fat purses, what are these compared to our vision of a happy and carefree world? They will tell you that you do not understand, but I understand perfectly: greed and lust are in your hearts, and desire rules your mind, and there is nothing more. Feelings have faded along with the glitter of gold, freedom has withered along with the will to conquer and destroy all that belongs to others, and joy lies only in inflicting suffering and fulfilling the promises of envy. Sad, oh so sad are your eyes, deceptive and deceitful. Power and ruthless authority, that is your religion!

They say that simple people resent the "better ones" because they envy them, but nothing could be further from the truth. This resentment stems from understanding a simple thing. Power is more than privilege and wealth. Therefore, I appeal to the masses of ordinary people, the ignorant masses: LET US FIGHT the boot of the fat haters who trample on our hearts. Let us fight for a place in this noble world!

The Innominate Ignorant (i.e. Smart Seditionist)"~
@500292 = ~Ode to Entropy~
@500293 = ~ODE TO ENTROPY
Weight: 0

"There is no turning back
Time is running out
Many a man has tried
But no one succeeded
Time goes only one way

Entropy
Entropy
Entropy
Entropy

Everything falls apart
Everything is receding
So deep in its heart
The multiverse is bleeding

The Inner and the Outer Planes
Energy and the Elements
The Astral Sea
Gate-towns going through shift
Toril and Oerth
And people are
So far
Away

Everything falls apart
Everything is receding
So deep in its heart
The multiverse is bleeding

Prepare for the endless night
At the Planes' extremity
No one sees the light
Behold entropy!"~
@500294 = ~Haer'Dalis' Head~
@500295 = ~HAER'DALIS' HEAD
Weight: 5

Such is the final fate of the Sigilian actor.~
@500296 = ~Scroll Case~
@500297 = ~SCROLL CASE
Weight: 2

This sturdy container allows dozens of scrolls to be placed inside it, protecting them from exposure to fire, rain, or lightning, common hazards faced by any adventuring wizard. ~
@500298 = ~Jade Cranium~
@500299 = ~JADE CRANIUM
Weight: 2

A cranium carved from a precious jade stone. The lower jaw is missing, leaving only the smooth, polished contours of the skull.~

////////////
// ====== //
