@901000 = ~^0xff78b570CONGRATULATIONS! 

You have reached the end of Act 1 of Blizzard in Baator. As you read these words, we are probably working hard on Acts 2 and 3 to release them as soon as possible.

In Act 2, you will of course see Cania in all its glory, and in Act 3, we will try to implement some of the original PS:T concepts that unfortunately did not make it into the final product due to time and budget constraints.

We hope you enjoyed what you saw and that you managed to catch at least half of the side content and hidden gems (of which there are many in Blizzard in Baator). Don't be afraid to tell us what you think about our demo or what could be changed or added, within reason, of course. You can reach us at: cania.believe.it@gmail.com 

If you want, you can also volunteer to help. Our project is 100% born out of passion, and not a single dollar has been spent on its creation. Only thousands of hours of free time spent by a few enthusiasts - CANIA BELIEVE IT WORKS. Among these enthusiasts are:

Project Lead:

    Filip "FallDamage312" Marczuk: lead developer, lead writer and story coordinator, visual design and execution, chief scriptwriter, translations and additional proofreading

Project developers:

    Filip "FallDamage312" Marczuk
    Kamil "Wrathu" Kwiatkowski: lead music composer and sound coordinator, writer, chief of inventory and items, translations and additional proofreading
    szef: project initiator, designer of the installer, structure, and menu elements, additional scriptwriter
    Alicja Wojciechowska: writer, tester, Polish and English editing and proofreading, additional translations

Editing and proofreading:

    Corpselight: editing and proofreading coordinator, Polish editing and proofreading, additional translations
    Brenda: Polish editing and proofreading
    Alexander Hurezeanu: English editing and proofreading
    Alderdash: English editing and proofreading
    Dune: English editing and proofreading
    Aquadrizzt: English editing and proofreading
    Inter: English editing and proofreading

Support:

    Darnath: organizational and merit-based support, walkthroughs, QA

Additional writers:

    Nordmarski,  Filip Cyrus Madej, Rafał Leniar, Pasza Mickiewicz, Tydeus

Sound and Music:

